{{infobox royalty | name = Adurfrazgird | title = Prince of [[Sasanian Empire]] | royal house = [[House of Sasan]] | father = [[Hormizd II]] | mother = Ifra Hormizd }}
'''Adurfrazgird''' was [[Sasanian Empire|Sasanian]] prince, who served as the governor of [[Nisibis]] under his brother [[Shapur II]] (r. 309-379). His name is derived from the [[Avestan]] {{transl|ae|frašō.kərəti}}, "Having the furtherance of Fire".
According to the Syriac Acts of the Persian Martyrs, the western frontier province of [[Arbayistan]] was divided in the 360s between Adurfrazgird and his brother Zamasp−Adurfrazgird governing Nisibis whilst Zamasp governed a area along the [[Tigris river]]. The two brothers were to keep an eye for each other and Roman activities. Zamasp was notably noted for his persecution of Christians.
